-- Deacon Patrol — Mayor's daemon patrol loop (26 steps).
-- The most complex molecule in Gas Town. Continuous patrol cycle.
-- Demonstrates: long sequential pipelines, script/LLM mix, decision cells,
-- parallel groups, patrol loop pattern, context management.
--
-- Step groups:
-- 1. Heartbeat + inbox (startup)
-- 2. Cleanup (orphan processes, test pollution)
-- 3. Gate evaluation + dispatch
-- 4. Health monitoring (convoys, deps, notifications)
-- 5. Infrastructure (dolt, zombies, plugins, dogs)
-- 6. Compaction (sessions, wisps, reports)
-- 7. Wrap-up (costs, digest, logs, context, loop)

## deacon-patrol

  -- === Group 1: Startup ===

  # heartbeat : script
    ```bash
    gt deacon heartbeat "starting patrol cycle"
    ```
  #/

  # inbox-check : llm
    - heartbeat
    system>
      You are the Deacon handling callbacks from agents.
      Clean up old wisps, then process inbox messages.
      Handle: HELP/escalation, LIFECYCLE, WARRANT results.
      Archive each message after handling.
    user>
      ```bash
      bd mol wisp gc --closed --force
      bd mol wisp gc --age 1h --force
      gt mail inbox
      ```
      Process each message by type. Archive when done.
    accept>
      All messages processed and archived.
  #/

  -- === Group 2: Cleanup ===

  # orphan-process-cleanup : script
    - inbox-check
    ```bash
    gt doctor -v 2>&1
    # Kill orphan Claude processes without tmux parents
    gt doctor --fix 2>/dev/null
    echo "orphan_cleanup_done"
    ```
  #/

  # test-pollution-cleanup : script
    - orphan-process-cleanup
    ```bash
    gt dolt status 2>&1
    # Check for orphan test databases
    gt dolt cleanup 2>/dev/null
    echo "test_cleanup_done"
    ```
  #/

  -- === Group 3: Gate evaluation + dispatch ===

  # gate-evaluation : llm
    - test-pollution-cleanup
    system>
      You evaluate molecules waiting at gates (approval, retry, timeout).
    user>
      Check for gated molecules:
      ```bash
      bd ready --json
      ```
      For each gated molecule, evaluate whether it should proceed.
    format> gates
      { evaluated: number, released: number, held: number }
  #/

  # dispatch-gated-molecules : script
    - gate-evaluation
    ```bash
    # Dispatch any molecules that passed gate evaluation
    echo "dispatch_complete"
    ```
  #/

  -- === Group 4: Health monitoring ===

  # check-convoy-completion : script
    - dispatch-gated-molecules
    ```bash
    gt convoy list --json 2>/dev/null | head -20
    echo "convoy_check_done"
    ```
  #/

  # resolve-external-deps : script
    - check-convoy-completion
    ```bash
    bd ready --json 2>/dev/null | head -20
    echo "deps_resolved"
    ```
  #/

  # fire-notifications : script
    - resolve-external-deps
    ```bash
    echo "notifications_done"
    ```
  #/

  -- === Group 5: Infrastructure (some can run in parallel) ===

  # heartbeat-mid : script
    - fire-notifications
    ```bash
    gt deacon heartbeat "mid-patrol"
    ```
  #/

  # health-scan : llm
    - heartbeat-mid
    system>
      You are scanning rig health: sessions, heartbeats, activity.
      Check each rig's witness, refinery, and polecats.
      Only report problems. Silence = healthy.
    user>
      For each rig, check:
      - Witness session alive + heartbeat fresh
      - Refinery session alive + heartbeat fresh
      - Active polecats status
      Restart any dead critical sessions.
    format> health
      { rigs_checked: number, issues: [{ rig: str, issue: str }] }
  #/

  # dolt-health : script
    - heartbeat-mid
    ```bash
    gt dolt status 2>&1
    echo "dolt_health_checked"
    ```

    ```oracle
    reject if output contains "unreachable";
    ```
  #/

  # zombie-scan : script
    - heartbeat-mid
    ```bash
    # Check for zombie sessions (alive but not working)
    for session in $(tmux list-sessions -F "#{session_name}" 2>/dev/null); do
      echo "session=$session"
    done
    echo "zombie_scan_done"
    ```
  #/

  # plugin-run : script
    - heartbeat-mid
    ```bash
    # Run registered daemon plugins
    echo "plugins_run"
    ```
  #/

  # dog-pool-maintenance : script
    - heartbeat-mid
    ```bash
    echo "dog_pool_ok"
    ```
  #/

  # dog-health-check : script
    - dog-pool-maintenance
    ```bash
    echo "dogs_healthy"
    ```
  #/

  -- === Group 6: Compaction ===

  # orphan-check : script
    - health-scan
    - dolt-health
    - zombie-scan
    - plugin-run
    - dog-health-check
    ```bash
    echo "orphan_check_done"
    ```
  #/

  # session-gc : script
    - orphan-check
    ```bash
    gt doctor --fix 2>/dev/null
    echo "session_gc_done"
    ```
  #/

  # wisp-compact : script
    - session-gc
    ```bash
    bd mol wisp gc --closed --force 2>/dev/null
    echo "wisp_compact_done"
    ```
  #/

  # compact-report : llm
    - wisp-compact
    system>
      You are summarizing compaction results. Be terse.
    user>
      Summarize: sessions gc'd, wisps compacted, orphans found.
    format> compact
      { sessions_gc: number, wisps_compacted: number, orphans: number }
  #/

  -- === Group 7: Wrap-up ===

  # costs-digest : script
    - compact-report
    ```bash
    echo "costs_logged"
    ```
  #/

  # patrol-digest : llm
    - costs-digest
    system>
      You are writing a patrol cycle digest. One paragraph max.
    user>
      Summarize this patrol cycle:
      - Gates evaluated: {{gate-evaluation.evaluated}}
      - Health issues: {{health-scan.issues}}
      - Compaction: {{compact-report}}
    format> digest
      { summary: str, issues_found: number, actions_taken: number }
  #/

  # log-maintenance : script
    - patrol-digest
    ```bash
    gt deacon heartbeat "patrol complete"
    echo "logs_maintained"
    ```
  #/

  # patrol-cleanup : script
    - log-maintenance
    ```bash
    bd mol wisp gc --closed --force 2>/dev/null
    echo "cleanup_done"
    ```
  #/

  # context-check : decision
    - patrol-cleanup
    system>
      You are checking whether the Deacon should loop or exit.
    user>
      Check context usage. If context is >80% full, exit for handoff.
      Otherwise, loop for another patrol cycle.
    format> verdict
      { action: "LOOP" | "EXIT", context_pct: number, reason: str }

    ```oracle
    json_parse(output);
    assert output.action in ["LOOP", "EXIT"];
    ```
  #/

  # loop-or-exit : script
    - context-check
    ```bash
    if [ "{{context-check.action}}" = "EXIT" ]; then
      gt mail send mayor/ -s "Deacon handoff" -m "Context at {{context-check.context_pct}}%. Handing off."
      echo "action=EXIT"
    else
      echo "action=LOOP"
      sleep 60
      echo "Ready for next patrol cycle."
    fi
    ```
  #/

  squash> trigger: on_complete template: patrol include_metrics: true

##/
